<div id="dummy-page">
  <h1>A page in your app</h1>
  <p>
    This might be something in your app that needs clarification or further<br />
    background, with an <%= dokno_article_link('in-context link like this one', slug: Dokno::Article.take&.slug) %>
    that explains it all.<br />
    Clicking that link opens a flyout within your app (to the right) containing<br />
    the article referenced by its unique slug or token.
  </p>

  <h2>Inline Article View Helper</h2>
  <p>
    You can add these in-context article links within your app via this Rails helper:
  </p>
  <p>
    &lt;%= dokno_article_link({link-text}, slug: {unique-article-slug}) %&gt;
  </p>

  <h2>Defined Articles</h2>
  <ul>
    <% Dokno::Article.select(:slug, :title).order(:title).each do |article| %>
      <li><%= dokno_article_link(article.title, slug: article.slug) %> (<%= article.slug %>)</li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>

  <h2>Link With Missing Slug</h2>
  <p>
    <%= dokno_article_link('Link to bogus slug', slug: '') %>
  </p>

  <h2>Link With Invalid Slug</h2>
  <p>
    <%= dokno_article_link('Link to bogus slug', slug: 'doesnotexist') %>
  </p>

  <hr />

  <p>
    <a target="_blank" href="<%= dokno_path %>">Open the knowledgebase site</a>
  </p>
</div>
